<p><strong>BTS reacts to possibly submitting ARIRANG to the Grammys</strong></p>

<p>Reflecting on the growing number of K-pop nominees at the <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/bts-members-custom-grammy-awards-performance-suits-to-be-exhibited-at-seouls-jewelry-museum-from-sept-to-dec-1323292">Grammy Awards</a>, including <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/grammys-2026-blackpinks-rose-makes-history-as-1st-k-pop-soloist-performing-kpop-demon-hunters-golden-locks-debut-win-1400390">Ros&eacute;</a>&rsquo;s two Big Four nods for APT. and KPop Demon Hunters&rsquo; total five, out of which they won one, RM shared with GQ, &ldquo;There are a lot of K-pop-related nominees you see in the general field and, really, I want to send big applause for them.&rdquo;</p>

<p>Sharing that the thought of winning a golden gramophone is still a goal for the team, the captain calls it far-fetched for the group. More than a month before the release of their 5th studio album, <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/arirang-diplo-confirms-work-on-bts-album-is-his-biggest-work-yet-says-it-will-shock-the-world-1400578">ARIRANG</a>, leader RM added, &ldquo;I mean, we&rsquo;ll try. Maybe we&rsquo;ll submit our album to the Grammys again. But I don&rsquo;t know, we don&rsquo;t want to be desperately eager for it&hellip;. We don&rsquo;t want to say anymore like, &lsquo;Ah, man, we want the Grammys.&rsquo; I mean, it doesn&rsquo;t mean that we really don&rsquo;t want it&mdash;but we&rsquo;ll try. But if not, then okay.&rdquo;</p>

<p>BTS nabbed a nomination for Dynamite in 2021 and then for Butter in 2022, and finally three more in 2023 for Yet To Come, My Universe with Coldplay, and Music of the Spheres as a featured artist, but walked away empty-handed all times, infuriating their fans.&nbsp;</p>

<p>However, the group seems to be more than accepting of their missed chance with the Recording Academy&rsquo;s awards, and although it is one of the accolades they haven&rsquo;t managed to grab so far, they&rsquo;re not heavily relying on it. &ldquo;Now, the most important thing is just that we are here back together again, we&rsquo;re going to see the fans all over the world,&rdquo; concluded RM.</p>
]]></description><link>https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/bts-reveals-if-theyll-submit-arirang-for-grammy-rm-reacts-to-k-pop-nods-dont-want-to-be-desperately-1400723</link><guid  isPermaLink="false">pinkvilla-1400723</guid><pubDate>Fri, 13 Feb 2026 18:23:43 +05:30</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[BTS reveals how members reacted to RM’s thoughts of ‘disband or take hiatus’ on livestream: ‘It’d be weird if you…’]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="https://www.pinkvilla.com/images/2026-02/2134786552_bts.webp"></img><p>BTS is gearing up for their next big move. Ahead of releasing their fifth studio album, <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/is-bts-filming-arirang-comeback-music-video-in-lisbon-fans-spot-group-at-dubai-airport-layover-1400436">ARIRANG</a>, the group is sharing their thoughts on being away from the limelight for so long, owing to their military enlistments, and on their return, leader RM spoke up about feeling the pressure from all around the world for a banging comeback. He opened up about considering a hiatus and even disbandment, which surprised millions. Now, fellow bandmates shared with GQ how they took the fun route instead of taking it too seriously.</p>

<p><strong>BTS reveals how they coped with RM&rsquo;s honest live session</strong></p>

<p>Back in December 2025, <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/why-did-rm-say-its-time-to-disband-bts-know-truth-behind-hilarious-livestream-exchange-with-jimin-1398647">RM</a> had spoken about how massive the pressure is for the group. While contemplating whether to go for sleeping pills, while wondering if the team should take a break or break up, after all, the singer managed to shock their millions of fans. However, the other <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/bts-to-walk-kings-road-during-gwanghwamun-square-comeback-live-heres-what-we-know-1400450">BTS</a> members, the only people who could understand just exactly what was going through the leader&rsquo;s mind, decided to take it in stride. Making fun of the situation, they shared memes of the day.</p>

<p>&ldquo;Actually, none of us watched that video of the live-streaming,&rdquo; V shared, who admitted that being the captain of the ship comes with more pressure for the 31-year-old, with Jin adding that they had only witnessed short-form content versions of the livestream. SUGA added that the members don&rsquo;t often consume each other&rsquo;s chats with their fans, and it&rsquo;d be &lsquo;weird&rsquo; to watch it. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re always together, and we&rsquo;re like brothers.&rdquo;</p>

<p>Clarifying that it was indeed RM&rsquo;s deep honesty with the ARMY and his way of being vulnerable, the team resorted to making fun of him for it instead of calling him out, terming his vulnerability as his love language. Jimin shared that the group isn&rsquo;t the type to console each other, &ldquo;But we just laugh and make fun of the person to make him laugh and forget about it&hellip;. We also had some drinks together. Booze always works.&rdquo;</p>

<p>The group, although also affected themselves, decided to focus on meme-making and pretending that nothing happened.&nbsp;</p>
