<p><strong>BLACKPINK&rsquo;s Ros&eacute; locks big Grammys night moment</strong></p>

<p>Ros&eacute; will make history this week, and we&rsquo;re all waiting for it. Set to become the first solo K-pop star to perform at the Recording Academy&rsquo;s biggest night of the year, the BLACKPINK member has been announced as one of the most-awaited performers of the show. She will join the likes of previously confirmed names, Lady Gaga, Justin Bieber, Sabrina Carpenter, Addison Rae, Alex Warren, KATSEYE, Leon Thomas, Lola Young, Olivia Dean, Clipse, Pharrell Williams, sombr, The Mar&iacute;as, Andrew Watt, Brandy Clark, Chad Smith, Duff McKagan, Lukas Nelson, Ms. Lauryn Hill, Post Malone, Reba McEntire, Slash, and Tyler, The Creator.&nbsp;</p>

