<p>Appearing on SBS PowerFM&rsquo;s Cultwo Show, she spoke about her latest song Good Goodbye starring Park Jung Min. &ldquo;When I first wrote the song, many people asked me, &lsquo;Can a good goodbye even exist? I&rsquo;ve never experienced one, so I don&rsquo;t understand.&rsquo; But after releasing it, a lot of listeners said they could receive the message positively, even if they haven&rsquo;t personally experienced a good goodbye.&rdquo; She added that it has made her proud of her music.&nbsp;</p>

<p>On being asked whether good goodbyes exist in real life and if she had ever experienced it herself, the singer, disagreeing with the other guest, shared that, &ldquo;I think it&rsquo;s possible [to have clean breakups].&rdquo; When the host shared that &lsquo;breaking up might be for the best&rsquo; in cases where, despite love, there&rsquo;s stress, Hwasa reacted with a small &lsquo;yes&rsquo; and ended up laughing out loud, cheering for the response.&nbsp;</p>

