<p><strong>Ros&eacute; breaks barriers and records with a quick whip of her two wrists and the magic of Bruno Mars</strong><br />
Following Ros&eacute;&rsquo;s achievement, the list of the fastest music videos by K-pop acts to reach 2 billion views in history on YouTube now go as Ros&eacute; and Bruno Mars&rsquo; APT. in just 334 days, PSY&rsquo;s Gangnam Style in 684 days, BLACKPINK&rsquo;s DDU-DU DDU-DU in 1663 days, BTS&rsquo; Dynamite in 1840 days, and finally BLACKINK&rsquo;s Kill This Love in 1975 days. Visibly, the girl group has managed to land 2 top 5 hits on the list, with a member grabbing the top spot separately. A truly remarkable feat, we must say!</p>

<p>With this, Ros&eacute; and Bruno Mars&rsquo; APT. joins Luis Fonsi&rsquo;s Despacito, Ed Sheeran&rsquo;s Shape of You, and Maroon 5 feat. Cardi B&rsquo;s Girls Like You, as&nbsp;the only music videos to reach 2 billion views on YouTube in under one year of release.</p>

<p>The song recently gave Ros&eacute; her first solo win at the <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/hollywood/2025-mtv-vmas-full-winners-list-lady-gaga-ariana-grande-blackpinks-rose-grab-major-trophies-1396563">2025 MTV Video Music Awards</a>, being given the prestigious <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/blackpinks-rose-quotes-therapist-after-apts-historic-song-of-the-year-win-at-2025-vmas-not-giving-up-1396567">Song of the Year win</a>. She is also a frontrunner in the Grammy Awards race, with many critics showing her as a strong contender for major categories, including collaboration and record of the year. If nominated, she would become the only one from her team and the first female K-pop star to do so.</p>
