<p><strong>BTS wants CORTIS to be humble and adaptive, much like themselves</strong><br />
Talking to Rolling Stone about their upcoming highly anticipated debut, <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/bts-and-txts-junior-group-at-bighit-music-confirms-name-cortis-to-debut-on-august-18-heres-all-we-know-1395213">CORTIS</a> shared the advice from other HYBE artists or BIGHIT MUSIC artists that has remained with them. As revealed by leader Martin, the seniors from the same label, <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/bts-v-reveals-he-cried-watching-jungkook-j-hope-and-jin-perform-together-too-embarrassed-1395443">BTS</a>, who have built themselves up from the bottom, showed their down-to-earth nature once again by saying, &ldquo;&lsquo;Do well by the people that you&#39;re working with, the staff.&rsquo; And I feel like that&#39;s all that matters. To hit a long run, you&#39;ve got to be good to the people around you. You&#39;ve got to show love.&rdquo;&nbsp;<br />
